-- All Blacks Pick Bird, Halai for Rugby Test Debuts Against Japan
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-10-30T21:38:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-30/all-blacks-pick-bird-halai-for-rugby-test-debuts-against-japan.html
New Zealand named the following team
to play Japan in their Nov. 2 rugby union Test at Prince
Chichibu Memorial Stadium in Tokyo:  Beauden Barrett, Charles Piatau, Ben Smith, Francis Saili,
Frank Halai, Dan Carter, Tawera Kerr-Barlow, Richie McCaw
(captain), Sam Cane, Steven Luatua, Domonic Bird, Jeremy Thrush,
Ben Franks, Dane Coles, Wyatt Crockett.  Reserves: Andrew Hore, Jeffery Toomaga-Allen, Charlie
Faumuina, Brodie Retallick, Luke Whitelock,  Aaron Smith , Tom
Taylor, Ryan Crotty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dan Baynes in Sydney at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  